text: L6.12. FIFO Cache Replacement Assume you are given a tiny 4-element, fully-associative cache that uses FIFO replacement. The cache stores single byte values (i.e., a line is a single byte). If the cache is empty at the beginning of execution, how many misses will the following string of accesses produce?
